	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, they used to do this kind of stuff for marketing. I doubt many people buying games back then had any idea of what a "megabit" (I believe SEGA used only the word "mega") actually was, they just knew that game x had more megabits than game y, so it was probably better.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
